Lymphatic permeation or poor differentiation warrants surgery due to the high risk of lymph node metastasis, mainly in >SM1 cancers. In the remaining cases, en-bloc and R0 resections determine low risk of residual lesion in the wall. Our scores can be a useful tool for the management of patients submitted to non-curative colorectal ESDs.
